records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which amends count 1 to misdemeanor criminal trespass to dwelling, contrary to Section 943.14 of the Wisconsin Statutes.
NO CONTEST pleas entered to the amended charge in count 1 and to the charge in count 3.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, criminal damage to property.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1)\ Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Have no contact with Cody Piontek and Joseph Rank or their residences and have no contact with Pawn America;
3) Have no contact with the co-defendant, Justin Anderson;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) provide DNA sample;
9) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
10) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling or work search;
11) Defendant is to testify against the co-defendant completely, truthfully and accurately if necessary;
12) Pay restitution of  $353.00 to Pawn America and $30.00 to Joseph Rank.  Restitution is ordered joint and several with Justin Anderson.
Minutes.
